snippet: A determination by the Senate parliamentarian complicates voting issues surrounding the latest challenge to the president’s signature legislation.
abstract: Senate leaders reveal that chamber parliamentarian Elizabeth MacDonough has ruled that some of provisions contained within House-passed budget reconciliation bill repealing aspects of Affordable Care Act do not qualify for expedited proceedings; ruling means Republicans in Senate would have to obtain supermajority of 60 votes to repeal individual and employer mandates.
lead_paragraph: A determination by the Senate parliamentarian complicates voting issues surrounding the latest challenge to the president’s signature legislation.
